snippet.textDisplay: Losing my best friend, Mohidul, on his 41st birthday shattered our 28-year friendship on 30th March'2024. We bonded over childhood memories, Biryani, and transcended religious differences since I was born in a liberal Brahmin family and he was a progressive Muslim. His passing has left me devastated, as he was my only friend from class 6. The song brings solace to my grief. My mother still can't accept Mohidul's death, good that Mohidul will meet my father in some heaven. Rest in peace, Mohidul Sardar. I wish I could have played you this song, just like we began our friendship with a Md. Rafi song 'suhani raat dhal chuki,  najane tum kab ayoge' ... .
